Selenium Web Automation Project

This project automates a scenario on Google Books using Selenium WebDriver and Java.

Scenario

1. Open a web browser and navigate to link "https://books.google.co.in/" i.e. Google Books.
2. Search for the keyword "Software Testing".
3. Filter by "Any Document = Books".
4. Click on the 3rd search result.
5. Take a screenshot of the book.

Prerequisites

- Java JDK
- Eclipse IDE
- Selenium WebDriver
- ChromeDriver

Setup Instructions

1. Clone the repository:
    git clone https://github.com/Nitin-Sehrawat/GoogleBooksDemo

2. Open the project in Eclipse:
    - Open Eclipse IDE.
    - Go to 'File -> Open Projects from File System'.
    - Select the cloned project directory.

3. Add below mentioned dependencies in pom.xml which are required for this project:
    <dependency>
			<groupId>org.seleniumhq.selenium</groupId>
			<artifactId>selenium-java</artifactId>
			<version>4.18.0</version>
		</dependency>

		<dependency>
			<groupId>org.testng</groupId>
			<artifactId>testng</artifactId>
			<version>7.9.0</version>
			<scope>test</scope>
		</dependency>
		
		<dependency>
			<groupId>commons-io</groupId>
			<artifactId>commons-io</artifactId>
			<version>2.15.1</version>
		</dependency>


Running the Tests

1. Run the 'GoogleBookSearch_testng.xml' file:
    - Right-click on the 'TestNG.xml' file in Eclipse.
    - Select 'Run As -> TestNG Suite'.

2. Check the output:
    - The script will take a screenshot of the book and save it as 'book_screenshot.png' in the project directory's ScreenShots folder.

